Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum finished with 28 points, six rebounds, nine assists, and two steals while shooting 10/21 from the field and 6/14 from the three-point range in 30 minutes of playing time.
The Boston Celtics dominated and won by a score of 123-93 despite playing without Jaylen Brown.
Post-Match Reflections: Jayson Tatum expressed regret for not greeting Killer Mike, who was court-side during the game.
The Celtics improved to 7-1 in their first eight games of the new season.
The Hawks dropped to 3-5 in their first eight games.
